The paper deals with designing a compact-support biorthogonal transform for graph signals using graph filterbanks. This involves coarsening the graph by defining supernodes for connected subgraphs and deriving edges from the connectivity between subgraphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Signal Processing (cs.SI), Information Theory (cs.IT), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as these areas deal with signal processing, data compression, and pattern recognition. Additionally, the paper also involves graph theory and algorithms for coarsening graphs, which could place it in the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA).
